Alcan Aluminium Ltd said it has cut theexpected cost of its planned Laterriere, Quebec, smelter byusing enhanced Grande Baie reduction technology.    The company said the decision to use prebaked anodetechnolgy used at its Grande Baie, Quebec, and Sebree, Ky.,smelters was taken primarily for cost reasons.    As a result, it said, the estimated total cost of theplanned smelter will be held to 450 mln U.S. dlrs, the low endof the range estimated in mid-May, while the cost of the firstphase was cut to 150 mln dlrs from the projected 175-225 mlndlrs. Reuter&#3;